## 5 Plugins That Power Our WordPress Sites in 2025

Building a WordPress site in 2025? Whether you're a DIY business owner or working with a web agency like [NC Digital](/), having the right plugin stack makes all the difference. Too many plugins slow your site down — but the right ones boost SEO, speed, security, and functionality.

Here are 5 essential (and mostly free) WordPress plugins we install on almost every site we build for South Wales businesses.

> "A good plugin should make your site faster, easier to manage, or more visible. These five do all three — without bloating your site."
> NC Digital

#### 1. LiteSpeed Cache

This is our go-to caching plugin for performance. It dramatically improves page load times, integrates with QUIC.cloud CDN, and optimises CSS, JS, and images — perfect for Core Web Vitals. If you're on a host that supports LiteSpeed (like [Krystal Hosting](https://krystal.uk)), it's a no-brainer.

#### 2. Yoast SEO

One of the most trusted SEO plugins in WordPress. It helps with meta titles, descriptions, XML sitemaps, and structured data. We use it to make sure each post and page is optimised for Google. Just remember to disable Yoast's Open Graph tags if using a dedicated social plugin like below.

#### 3. Open Graph and Twitter Card Tags

This simple plugin ensures every page and blog post displays the correct image and description when shared on platforms like Facebook or X (Twitter). You can set a sitewide default too — helpful for maintaining brand consistency. We use it alongside Yoast by disabling Yoast's OG output.

#### 4. 404 Solution

Redirects broken or mistyped URLs to the correct page automatically — or logs them so you can manually fix them. It helps prevent SEO loss and improves the user experience. No more visitors landing on dead ends!

#### 5. Forminator

Our favourite contact form builder. It's easy to style, responsive, and includes lead capture, quizzes, and polls — all for free. We use it to create enquiry forms that integrate with email marketing or CRM tools.

#### Bonus Mentions

- **LoginPress** – Brand your login screen and improve security
- **Child Theme Configurator** – Safely create and edit child themes
- **Admin and Site Enhancements** – Powerful toolkit to streamline your dashboard

#### Final Thoughts

There are thousands of WordPress plugins — but most websites only need a lean stack that improves speed, SEO, UX, and leads. These 5 give you exactly that.

